{"parentUuid":"e9c684b9-4b0a-4a90-8358-a11405190277","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccxxb3ueB2B8GqCVnamJr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The dashboard is live on the canvas with both datasets held in state, so future updates can append rather than re-render from scratch.\n\n**What's on it**\n\nThe chart is a line chart of errors per minute, seeded with your five points (2, 3, 1, 4, 2) labeled `T-4` through `T-0`. It reads from `$state.errorRate`, where each entry is `{ minute, errors }`. The table below it lists the three most recent log lines, reading from `$state.logs`, where each entry is `{ level, message }` — split that way so the level renders as its own column rather than being baked into the message text.\n\n**Appending later**\n\nTo push a new data point, append an object to the `errorRate` state path (for example `{ minute: \"T+1\", errors: 5 }`); the chart re-renders from that array on every change. Same idea for `logs` — prepend or append a `{ level, message }` object depending on whether you want newest-first. If you want the log table capped at three rows, that trimming has to happen wherever the append is done, since the table just displays whatever the array holds."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":913,"cache_read_input_tokens":4474,"output_tokens":338,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":913,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":4474,"cache_creation_input_tokens":913,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":913},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccxxb2xbF78CRmveFvk4p","attributionMcpServer":"canvas","at